This week in my Homeland Security Committee hearing, I talked about the Port of Houston, a major driver of jobs and economic growth, and how we’re using too many cranes made in China. 

I pushed for investing in making them here at home and raised concerns about cutting aid to Latin America, which only helps China expand its influence. We should be looking out for hard working Americans and their jobs.

