Last week, during my Homeland Security Committee hearing, I addressed the growing cybersecurity crisis. 

With 500,000 jobs unfilled, we must act now to train our workforce and recruit talent from all backgrounds, including HBCUs and technical schools, to protect sensitive information and strengthen our defenses.

@HomelandDems

Joining my Democratic colleagues to back the Taxpayer Data Protection Act. We're fighting to protect your privacy and stop reckless efforts to let billionaire tech guy Elon Musk access your confidential records, threatening Social Security & Medicare. Not now, not ever.

